README
~~~~~~

Testing the Source 

1. Prepare input for cortx_setup. There are two files in this folder. 
   a. cluster.conf 
   b. config.conf

2. Make sure PYTHON_PATH includes src folder, if you are not using rpm.

3. Run apply command 
   $ cortx_setup.py config apply yaml://`pwd`/config.yaml yaml://`pwd`/cluster.yaml yaml:///tmp/mp.conf

4. Run bootstrap command
   $ cortx_setup.py cluster bootstrap yaml:///tmp/mp.conf

   output will look something like this...
    motr_setup --config yaml:/etc/cortx/cortx.conf --services io
    hare_setup --config yaml:/etc/cortx/cortx.conf --services all
    s3_setup --config yaml:/etc/cortx/cortx.conf --services io,auth,bg_consumer
    utils_setup --config yaml:/etc/cortx/cortx.conf --services message_bus
    csm_setup --config yaml:/etc/cortx/cortx.conf --services agent
    motr_setup --config yaml:/etc/cortx/cortx.conf --services fsm
    s3_setup --config yaml:/etc/cortx/cortx.conf --services bg_producer

